main event: On March 4, 1966, two round objects emitting a bright bluish-white light were observed for about two hours in Oswego, New York.
interesting points: The objects were described as circular and giving off a bright light., The sighting lasted approximately two hours and included two witnesses., The objects seemed to resemble an aircraft but disappeared quickly., A rumbling sound was heard by the witnesses, described as strange and silent., The Air Force was notified on the same day after the sighting.
sighted object: two round objects emitting bluish-white light
witness description: The witnesses were friends observing the objects from a distance, noting a strange light and sound.
